    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-09-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="443" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 271.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 25, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of the 2d
                            instant, No. 168, enclosing copies of the replies which you made, in
                            compliance with my instructions, to the letters of condolence and
                            sympathy which were inspired by the death of the late President, and
                            addressed to this government by various political and social
                            organizations in France. In reply, I beg that you will accept my thanks
                            for the prompt and efficient manner in which you performed the duty
                            assigned to you, and I desire, at the same time, to inform you of my
                            high appreciation of the communications which you have been pleased to
                            submit to me as the result of your labor.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
